===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[teleological]] [[argument]]}}

# {{context|philosophy|theology}} A type of argument for the [[existence]] of [[God]], advanced by a number of [[philosophers]], including [[w:Thomas Aquinas|Thomas Aquinas]] and [[w:George_Berkeley|George Berkeley]], which maintains that the [[design]] of the [[world]] reveals that objects have [[purpose]]s or [[end]]s and that such an [[organized]] design must be the [[creation]] of a [[supreme]] designer (God).  Also called the [[argument from design]].

